# Project Guidelines

## Environment & Tooling
- **Package Manager:** `pnpm` - Run `pnpm install` to setup dependencies
- **Type Checking:** `tsc --noEmit` - TypeScript compiler in check-only mode (DO NOT use `tsc` alone)
- **Linting:** `eslint <path> [--fix]` - JavaScript/TypeScript linting
- **Formatting:** `prettier --write <path>` - Code formatting (if configured)
- **Build:** DO NOT run `pnpm build` or `vite build` automatically. Only build when explicitly requested
- **Testing:** `vitest` (if configured) - Unit test pure logic, integration test components/hooks

## Style & Conventions
- **TypeScript/React:** Functional components, TypeScript strict mode, descriptive names, small deterministic functions
- **Types:** Prefer explicit types; avoid `any`; use interfaces for objects, type aliases for unions
- At each /spec stage run `eslint --fix` + `tsc --noEmit` on touched files

## Core Principles
- Verify over assume: Always double-check, research patterns first
- Failures first: Lead with errors, no optimistic language with failures
- Always re-raise: Never swallow exceptions - let them propagate

